### 5. Eager Test — `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (lines 57–63)

Calls **7** distinct production methods (`ValidateOrder`, `CalculateTotal`, `ApplyDiscount`, `ReserveInventory`, `ProcessPayment`, `SendConfirmation`, `UpdateOrderHistory`) then asserts a single status. If this fails, you have no idea which step broke.

**Fix:** Test each step independently. If a full-workflow integration test is desired, name it explicitly and add per-step assertions:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ProcessPayment_ValidOrder_SetsPaymentConfirmed()
{
    // Setup: a validated order with a calculated total
    var processor = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory);
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-1", 2) }, TotalAmount = 50m };

    processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));

    Assert.AreEqual("PaymentConfirmed", order.PaymentStatus);
}
