| Priority | Smell | Fix | Why first |
|----------|-------|-----|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add assertions | Currently gives **false confidence** — a passing test that verifies nothing |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into deterministic tests | **Hides bugs** — test can never fail on status |
| 3 | Mystery Guest | Inline test data | **Broken on CI** — hard-coded `C:\` path fails everywhere except one machine |
| 4 | Sleepy Test | Await instead of sleep | **Flaky + slow** — 2s delay per run, still non-deterministic |
| 5 | Eager Test | Split into focused tests | Difficult to diagnose failures |
| 6 | Exception Handling | Use `Assert.ThrowsException` | Quick 2-line refactor, better failure messages |
| 7 | Magic Numbers | Use named constants | Improves readability, ~5 min fix |
| 8 | Sensitive Equality | Assert on properties | Prevents brittle formatting breaks |
